Title: Fed lowers rates, but Powell suggests move may be the last of 2025
Description: A policy divide within the central bank and a lack of federal government data may put another interest rate cut out of reach this year, Fed Chair Powell said.
Publish Time: 2025-10-29T05:02:25.373Z
Content: *   Summary
*   Companies

*   US central bank cuts rates by a quarter of a percentage point
*   Fed Governor Miran, Kansas City Fed President Schmid dissent
*   Policy decision was made in the absence of key government data
*   Fed's balance sheet drawdown halted
*   Powell says there are 'strongly differing views' within Fed about a December rate cut

WASHINGTON, Oct 29 (Reuters) - A policy divide within the U.S. central bank and a lack of [federal government data](https://www.reuters.com/world/us/us-government-shutdown-threatens-spending-power-congress-2025-10-26/) may put another interest rate cut out of reach this year, Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell said on Wednesday, as he acknowledged the threats that officials see to the job market but also the risky nature of making further rate moves without a fuller picture of the economy.

The Fed on Wednesday cut interest rates by a quarter of a percentage point, as expected, as a way to temper any further weakening of the job market...
